REVIEW: BORDERLANDS 3

Borderlands 3 chega às mãos do público quase cinco anos após Borderlands: The Pre-Sequel (2014), último lançamento central da franquia com o mesmo estilo de jogabilidade. O game está disponível para Xbox One, PS4, PC (via Epic Games Store) e será lançado futuramente para Google Stadia.

O mais recente shooter looter da 2K Games e Gearbox Software traz um alívio para os fãs do gênero e da série, com conteúdo e diversão de sobra. Apesar disto, o título também incita o questionamento sobre a necessidade de amadurecimento (literal) de uma franquia prestes a completar 10 anos.

Borderlands 3 é um divertido shooter looter, com diversas opções de gameplay dependendo do seu próprio gosto, bem como uma aplausível variedade de localidades a serem exploradas, missões a serem cumpridas e armas a serem usadas. No entanto, o estúpido humor da série permanece intacto, senão retrógrado, e infelizmente descredibiliza o que poderia ter sido uma narrativa minimamente interessante com uma rasa crítica ao comportamento virtual-viciado da sociedade moderna. As tentativas de piadas são, na maioria, imbecis e irritantes. Ignorando os diálogos putrefeitos, a jogabilidade é, em geral, equilibrada e engajante apesar da repetição de fases e de inimigos. Há também muitos bugs pelo caminho, com apenas alguns danificando, de fato, a experiência de jogo.

NOTA: 70/100 - BOM

caption.text:
August and September where full of events, but no matter how late it is from actual event, I will still post some impressions from #gamescom2019
Because there is nothing more precious than to stay true to the geek I am 😅
Unfortunately we did not manage to get into #cyberpunk2077 booth, the line you see is already 5-6 hour of waiting time... but what we managed to see and try out during these two days of #gaming:
1. Pagan Online - smth new for me from #wargaming
2. World of Tanks - our classic, it is already a tradition to visit the booth of this Belarusian gamedesigner :)
3. Humankind
4. Two point hospital - did u also play this gem on PS2 :B suuuuper fun
5. Darksiders Genesis
6. Watch Dogs Legion
7. Medieval - also a cute game from PS2
8. Hands-free gaming- see the video impression, your eyes control the game
9. Biomutant
10. Monkeyking
And some other fun mini and not so mini games.
We wanted to try out Doom, Borderlands 3, but wait in the line for 3 or more hours seemed too much of time waste, there is so much more to explore at Gamescom, so rather give a chance to small gamedevs, indie village or scatter around the merch area.

It’s official... #mythiitzdoesinktober is BACK! 😱
.
.
I tried and failed last year, but this year I’m really gonna give it my all! My goal is to post one picture a day for the month of October. I am following the official prompts, but the catch is I’m drawing all my video game characters that you have grown to love! 🥰
.
.
It’s really crazy to think that I used to do art as my main source of (unsustainable) income, but I really haven’t been creating anything new in the past few years. I’m going from 0 to 100, and I really need your love and support! 😭
.
.
Tomorrow begins DAY ONE, which is the RING theme. It should be pretty familiar for longtime fans ☺️💎💍
.
.

caption.text:
Avez-vous passé un bon week-end ?
Moi ? J’en ai profité pour faire une petite escapade à #Cocolint 🏝
Car, même si j’y retourne assez régulièrement, j’ai été complètement conquise par ce remake : j’avais beau me savoir en terrain connu, j’ai apprécié le fait de redécouvrir l’île sous un tout nouvel aspect et d’explorer tous ses secrets, une fois de plus 💕
En observant l’Oeuf du Poisson-Rêve depuis la Plage Coco, j’ai eu une pensée émue pour tous ceux qui ont foulés ces terres pour la première fois ces derniers jours. J’espère que vous avez vécu la plus belle de toutes vos aventures et qu’elle vous marquera profondément, comme cela fut mon cas il y a vingt-cinq ans de ça.
Au loin, le cri d’une mouette résonne dans le ciel azur, comme pour faire écho à une ancienne promesse. Le sourire aux lèvres, je sais que je ne l’ai jamais oublié... 🐚
.
.
.

Creating something is a very rewarding feeling...however, it's increasily difficult to design something that hasn't already been thought of. This applies for many careers, especially music. Every song you could think of has probably been constructed - so what are you going to do that separates you from the rest?

Putting your own twist on an already-produced item is more acceptable nowadays, so don't be discouraged to build something from scratch, even if it's as simple as this washing machine - plus, learning from previous successful inventions will help guide a triumphant brand-new product!
.
.

caption.text: Fun

When I was younger, I had a dangerous access to eBay, and as such, would save up money to buy things related to gaming I couldn’t find anywhere else. At this time, I was super deep into both FFVIII and a big breakup, so this retail therapy that allowed me access to Squall’s necklace was something I grew pretty attached to. I don’t wear it now, but it’s a piece I remember fondly, and it signifies something pretty important for the time. Thanks, Griever! -
